text:
That's the cycle.  People use a word to simply define a demographic, condition, affliction etc.  A few years pass and people declare that word to be offensive and demand that everyone use a different word.  A few more years pass and that word is "offensive", so a new word has to be selected, which will also only last a few years before some stupid snowflakes decide that saying THAT word is borderline hate speech.

People who do not have homes are homeless.  That's just how the grammar works.  There's nothing offensive about it.  It just looks offensive because there are people who have offensive opinions.  Changing the word will just mean those offensive people have a new word to use offensively.  Stop pretending changing language will change attitudes.
